To the fans and FIAF3 community,

I'm disappointed that we won't be racing in Imola, but it was the right decision not to go forward with this weekend's events. The emergency personnel will be much better utilized giving relief to the people of the region around Imola, instead of devoting time and resources to the Grand Prix. My thoughts and prayers go to those affected by the flooding in Imola.

My team and I are looking forward to going racing again in Monaco.

Sincerely,
Hunter Yeany

Due to unforeseen circumstances, I regret to share that the Austrian GP was my last race of the 2023 FIAF3 Championship Season. 

RODIN Carlin has played an integral part in my motorsport career. As I’ve shared many times, Carlin was the first team I tested with in Europe at 14 and it meant a lot to me to drive for them this season. I am grateful to Trevor Carlin for the opportunity and his confidence in me. I wish the best to everyone at RODIN Carlin and wish my teammates good luck! 

Motorsport is my life and I will continue to look toward the future, work hard, and take the necessary steps to reach Formula One.

I was so proud to be a part of the launch of @oy6bourbon !! This company is dedicated to Serving Those Who Serve our great country - and I'm so thankful for them.

The inspiration and admiration I have for all servicemen and women, especially my dad who was a US Navy SEAL, shape the way I lead my life with integrity, focus, and strength. Here is to all of you who have put it all on the line to protect us at home. I'll always be #OnYourSix
